CONTROLLER
->to set mode and numOfPlayers. Called by message
setGameStatus()

->to set a player deck. Called by message
setDeck(Player nick, String deck)

->to set a player tower. Called by message
setTower(Player nick, String tower)

->to set chosen SupportCard. Called by message
setChosenSupportCard( int card)

->to determine round order. Called by method
calculateRoundOrder()

->to activate CharacterCard
activateCharacterCard(CharacterCard)

->to move students from the hall to the dining hall. Called by message
moveStudentsHToD(Arraylist<StudentColor> students)

->to move students from the hall to (single or multiple) island(s). Called by message
moveStudentsHToI(Integer island, ArrayList<StudentColor> students)

->to remove students from the hall (the ones removed by the movements). Called by method
removeStudents(StudentColor color)

->to set the cloud where the client want to take the students. Called by message
setChosenCloud(int cloud)

->to assign a teacher. Called by method
assignTeacher()

->to set new mother nature position. Called by message
setMotherNatureMovements(int movements)

->to set that the current round is the last one. Called by method
  setLastRound()

->to notify that the game is over. Called by method
endGame()

->to determine winners and losers. Called by method
winners()


VIEW
->communicate to the client to insert the nickname. Called by message
askNickname()

->ask to the client if he want to choose a character card. Called by method
askActivateCharacterCard()

->communicate to the client to choose a character card. Called by method
askCharacterCard()

->choose the numOfPlayers and mode. (only to the first player connected). Called by message
askSetGameStatus()

->ask to set a color for the tower (the controller will notify if is correctly setted). Called by method
askTower()

->ask to choose a deck (the controller will do a check). Called by method
askDeck()


->ask to choose a support card (or nothing). Called by method
askSupportCard()

->ask to the client which students wants to move from H to D. Called by method
askMoveStudentsHToD()

->ask to the client which students wants to move from H to I (single or multiple). Called by method
askMoveStudentsHToI()

->ask to the client from which C wants to take the students. Called by method
askCloud()

->ask where he wants to put mother nature (the controller will do a check). Called by method
askMotherNatureMovements()

->show a message (string) on the client screen. Called by message
showString(String message )

->show the character card used by a player and his name. Called by message
showCharacterCard(Player nick, int id)

->show the support card used by a player and his name. Called by message
showSupportCard(Player nick, int id)

->show on the client screen which support card is using during that turn. Called by method
updateUsedSupportCard()

->show the available support card to the client. Called by method
updateAvailableSupportCards()

->show on screen the price of a specific character card. Called by message
updateCharacterCardPrice(int id)

->show the new position of mother nature (when other players changes it). Called by message
updateMotherPosition(int island)

->show the new color of the island for a tower. Called by message
updateTowerColor(String tower)

->show the island blocked. Called by message
updateBlock(int island, boolean blocked)

->merge two islands. Called by message
mergeIslands(int toBeMerged, int mergeTo)

->show the added students on a specific island. Called by message
addStudentsOnIsland(int island, ArrayList<StudentColor>)

->show the added students in the dining hall of the specified player. Called by message
addStudentToPlayerD(String nick, Arraylist<StudentColor>)

->show the winners and the losers. Called by message
showGameResults(ArrayList<String> winners, ArrayList<String> losers)

->remove the students from the dining hall of a specified player. Called by message
removeStudentsFromPlayerD(String nick,ArrayList<StudentColor>)

->update the hall of a specified player. Called by message
updatePlayerHall(String nick, ArrayList<StudentColor>)

->update the amount of coins that the player has. Called by message
updatePlayerCoins(String nick, int coin)

